foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: In the FY2015 Annual FOIA Report, OS reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY2015 as “99.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “24” requests is due to 24 requests pending from FY 2015 but not reported, which were fulfilled in FY 2016. The correct number is “123.” Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2016 for OS has been amended to “123” in the FY2016 Annual FOIA Report.

In the FY2015 Annual FOIA Report, ITA reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY2015 as “137.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “1” request is due to ITA determining in FY2016 that 1 pending request from FY2015 was closed in FY2015. The correct number is “136.” Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2016 for ITA has been amended to “136” in the FY2016 Annual FOIA Report.

In the FY2015 Annual FOIA Report, NIST reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY2015 as “41.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “1” request is due to NIST determining in FY2016 that 1 pending request from FY2015, which was under appeal, was closed on 05/05/15. The correct number is “40.” Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2016 for NIST has been amended to “40” in the FY2016 Annual FOIA Report.

In the FY2015 Annual FOIA Report, NOAA reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY2015 as “147.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “3” requests is due to NOAA determining in FY2016 that 3 requests were entered by both a requester and by NOAA, so “3” requests were closed as duplicate requests. The correct number is “144.” Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2016 for NOAA has been amended to “144” in the FY2016 Annual FOIA Report.

In the FY2015 Annual FOIA Report, the agency overall number of requests pending at the end of FY2015 was reported as “557.” Due to the amendment in the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2016 for OS, ITA, NTIS, and NOAA (see footnotes above), the agency overall number of requests pending as of the start of FY2016 has been amended to “576.”
